---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import CtaBand from '../../components/CtaBand.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Scam Resilience for Credit Unions | Spry"
  description="A member benefit that keeps savings where they belong. Spry trains older members to catch scams — co-branded to your credit union, with nothing for branch staff to run."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <p class="kicker">For credit unions</p>
      <h1>Protect the member, not just the account.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Financial safety is now part of every modern member relationship. Spry trains your older
        members to catch scams before the money leaves their account — so you reduce fraud
        losses, keep deposits where they belong, and earn loyalty across generations.
      </p>
      <p>
        Americans 60+ reported $7.75 billion lost to internet-enabled fraud in 2025, and every
        scammed member costs a credit union twice: first the drained deposits, then the fraud-ops
        hours, the hard conversations, and the shaken trust that follows. Fraud alerts and
        transaction monitoring catch some of it — after it starts. Spry works further upstream,
        training the member themselves to hang up before anything moves.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--paper">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2 style="max-width: 36rem;">Turn fraud prevention into member loyalty</h2>
      <div class="grid grid--3" style="margin-top: 36px;">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Reduce fraud before it hits</h3>
          <p>
            Every drill a member passes is a real scam they're readier for — including the ones
            that arrive by phone or text, where your transaction monitoring can't see until the
            money is already moving.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Retain deposits &amp; trust</h3>
          <p>
            A scammed member often drains savings, and a shaken member often leaves. Preventing
            one six-figure loss pays for years of the program — and the member who caught the scam
            tells everyone who helped them do it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Grow the next generation</h3>
          <p>
            The monthly Resilience Report goes to the family members your member chooses — a
            recurring, co-branded touchpoint that shows adult children a credit union that
            actually looks out for their family.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap prose">
      <h2>The benefit members talk about</h2>
      <p>
        Rate tables look the same everywhere. A credit union that <em>trains its members to beat
        scammers</em> — and proves it every month with a co-branded report — does not. Every drill
        caught is a quiet hero moment your brand shares credit for, and every briefing on the
        newest scams arrives with your name on it, reminding members and their families who's
        looking out for them. It's the people-helping-people story credit unions were built on,
        made visible every month.
      </p>

      <h2>Spry does the work — nothing for your staff to run</h2>
      <p>
        Spry runs quietly in the background: consent, drills, in-the-moment coaching, briefings,
        and the monthly Resilience Report are all handled by us. No core integration, no data
        feeds, and no access to accounts — Spry never touches money, which keeps vendor review
        and the compliance conversation short.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Offer Spry as a member benefit for members 65+, or as an opt-in perk</li>
        <li>Member and family consent handled by us</li>
        <li>
          You receive nothing about individual results unless the family opts to share — clean
          from a privacy and compliance standpoint
        </li>
        <li>
          Aggregate, anonymized reporting — including a marketing-able stat for your community:
          <em>“Our members identified 87% of simulated scams this quarter”</em>
        </li>
        <li>A dedicated onboarding partner, with co-branded enrollment materials for branches and newsletters</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Implementation is simple</h2>
      <p>
        One intro conversation and you're ready to roll Spry out to members. Volume pricing runs
        $4–8 per enrolled member per month, and founding-partner pilots are open for the first
        cohort of credit unions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand
    headline="Bring Spry to your members."
    body="A 20-minute call covers pricing, compliance posture, and how a pilot works."
    cta="Book a 20-minute call"
    href="mailto:hello@sawtoothtechnologies.com?subject=Spry%20credit%20union%20program"
  />
</Base>

<style>
  ul { padding-left: 1.2em; }
  ul li { margin-bottom: 0.6em; }
</style>
